						<summary>

						<p>V <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> south wall of the <hi rend="italic">Garuḍa-maṇḍapa</hi> of the Śrī Ranganatha temple.</p>						

						<p>16th-17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be assigned to the 16th century on internal evidence.</p>						

						<p>The records refers to names of the ladies viz., Nāchāramma, wife of Savaram Veṅkaṭappa nāyaka, Vōbulamma, wife of Komara Venkaṭappa nāyak, Chī(Sī)tamma, (wife) of Raghunātha-nāyaka and Venkaṭamma (wife) of Veṅkaṭappa nāyaka.</p>						

						<p>(Published is <hi rend="italic">South Indian Inscriptions</hi> Vol. XXIV, Ins No. 587, p 558.)</p>						

